         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Kirchheim via Minyip, ¶ 4 July, 1892. ¶ Highly esteemed Baron, ¶  ¶ With the departing mail I am sending you a plant for your kind identification. At first I believed it to be  ¶ Hypoxis glabella ¶ , ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">92.07.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Johann Eckert</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M6, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Pauridia glabella var. glabella</seg> (MEL 534341). MS annotation by M: 'Beantw. 5/7/92' [Replied 5/7/92]. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Kirchheim via Minyip.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">4 Juli 1892.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Sehr geehrter Herr Baron!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mit abgehender Post schicke ich Ihnen eine Pflanze zur gütigen Benennung zu. Ich glaubte anfangs dieselbe sei <name key="Hypoxis%20glabella">Hypoxis glabella</name>, allein es ist jetzt noch nicht die Blütezeit für selbige und sodann erscheint die Pflanze immer in dem Zustande wie das zugeschickten Exemplar sich befindet. Soweit wie ich sie bis jetzt beobachtet habe, finde ich, dass der </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Befruchtungszustand</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> der Blumen immer </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">in</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> der Erde stattfindet, und dass nach demselben die Samenkapsel aus dem Erdboden hervorkrümmt und meistens dann derselben Stengel in der Normalform eine horizontale Position annimmt. Die robusten Exemplare habe ich under <name key="Xertotes%20effusa">Xertotes effusa</name> gesammelt. Ich habe die Pflanze schon Anfang Mai d.J. gefunden, jetzt ist sie am häufigsten.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Geococcus pussilus kann ich nicht zum keimen kriegen. Der Samen muss mehr wie 8 Jahre alt sein. Vielleicht finde ich die Pflanze im September bei L. Albacutya.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wir haben herrliches, fruchtbares Wetter.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit herzlichstem Grusse</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. P. Eckert.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Kirchheim via Minyip,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Vic</seg>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4 July, 1892.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Highly esteemed Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With the departing mail I am sending you a plant for your kind identification. At first I believed it to be <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Hypoxis%20glabella">Hypoxis glabella</name>
               </seg>, however, this is not the flowering time for them, and in addition the plant is always found in the same state as the specimen sent. As far as I have observed to date, I find that the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fructification</hi>
               </seg> of the flower always occurs <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">in</hi>
               </seg> the soil, and that afterwards the seed capsule curves out of the soil, and usually the stem of the normal form then takes on a horizontal position. The robust specimens I have collected under <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Xertotes%20effusa">Xertotes effusa</name>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Xerotes effusa</seg>.</p>
               </note> I have found the plant already early in May of this year; now it is most frequent.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I cannot get <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Geococcus </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">pussilus</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">i.e. </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Geococcus </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">pusillus.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to germinate. The seed must be more than 8 years old. Perhaps I will find the plant near Lake Albacutya<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Vic.</p>
               </note> in September.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We have splendid, fruitful weather.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">With cordial greetings,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. P. Eckert.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Geococcus%20pusssilus">Geococcus pusssilus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hypoxis%20glabella">Hypoxis glabella</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Xertotes%20effusa">Xertotes effusa</name>
            </p>
         </div>
